Just two weeks after launching 4G+, which offers customers faster data speeds, MTN Nigeria has announced a price slash across all its data plans and offerings. Under the new price structure, customers can now enjoy more value for money with up to 30 per cent more data volume for 30-day plans.They will also enjoy up to 100 per cent incremental volume for weekly data plans and 25 per cent incremental volume for daily plans. In addition, new customers will enjoy introductory offers, with access to prices as low as N50 for 50MB and N500 for 2GB. They will also receive a 100 per cent bonus on data purchases for four months. Commenting on the affordable prices, the Chief Marketing Officer, Rahul De said: “With the faster internet speeds delivered by the launch of 4G+, this data price slash could not have come at a better time for our customers, as we’ve seen that faster data speeds means more data usage.” 